					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple with the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee from two local shepherds, made by <hi rend="bold">Chēdi-Mahādēviyār</hi> wife <hi rend="bold">of Siddavaḍattaḍigaḷ the chief of Malāḍu</hi>, on the day of a solar eclipse. (See <hi rend="bold">No. 293</hi> above). This is evidently an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
